Sometimes different parts of the code contain identical groups of variables
(such as parameters for connecting to a database).
These clumps should be turned into their own classes.

Whole Value: The general form: a quantity, and its unit.
"How far is my hotel? Its 400". This expression, without the unit, has no sense.

Data clumping solves this issue creating a class for a quantity and its unit.
Because a quantity always has to have an unit.
